  </head>
  <body>
    <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: EYE DISCHARGE</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site &amp; Laterality</span>
          <ul>
            <li>UNILATERAL </li>
            <ul>
              <li><span class="ophthalmology">Blocked Tear Duct (Dacrostenosis),
                  <br>
                </span></li>
              <li><span class="ophthalmology">Foreign Body, <br>
                </span></li>
              <li><span class="ophthalmology">Cellulitis</span></li>
            </ul>
            <li>BILATERAL </li>
            <ul>
              <li><span class="infectious">Viral or <br>
                </span></li>
              <li><span class="infectious">Allergic <br>
                </span></li>
              <li><span class="infectious">rarelly - Bacterial.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Is the discharge coming from one eye or both?"</span></div>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="obstetric ophthalmology emergency">first month of life </li>
            <ul>
              <li class="obstetric ophthalmology emergency"><b class="emergency">Ophthalmia
                  Neonatorum (Red Flag)</b></li>
            </ul>
            <li class="ophthalmology">first few months </li>
            <ul>
              <li class="ophthalmology"><b class="ophthalmology">Congenital
                  Blocked Tear Duct</b></li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
          <ul>
            <li class="infectious respiratory">Trigger</li>
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious respiratory">sick contacts, daycare, school
                outbreaks?</li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
              <li class="rheumatic environmental">New environmental exposures
                (pollen, animals, chlorine pools)?</li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious respiratory">Recent upper respiratory
                infection or cold symptoms?</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"When did you first notice the discharge? And how
          old is your child?"</span></div>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How many days has this been happening?"</span></div>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>: Aggravating &amp;
            Relieving Factors</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Does anything seem to make it worse, like rubbing
          the eyes? Does wiping it away help for a while?"</span></div>
      <!-- C: Character (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>: Character</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="ophthalmology">NATURE OF DISCHARGE
              <ul>
                <li><b>Watery (clear, tearing):</b> <b class="infectious">Viral
                    Conjunctivitis</b>, <b class="rheumatic">Allergic
                    Conjunctivitis</b>, <b class="ophthalmology">Blocked Tear
                    Duct</b></li>
                <li><b>Purulent (pus-like, thick, yellow/green):</b> <b class="infectious">Bacterial
                    Conjunctivitis</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li class="infectious emergency"><b><em><u>Gonococcal</u></em>:</b>
                      Profuse purulent discharge, <b class="emergency">Medical
                        Emergency</b></li>
                    <li class="infectious"><u>Pseudomonas</u><b>:</b> Greenish
                      discharge</li>
                    <li class="infectious"><b><em><u>Chlamydia</u></em>:</b>
                      Watery &rarr; purulent &rarr; bloody progression</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li><b>Mucoid (stringy, white, ropey):</b> <b class="rheumatic">Hallmark
                    of Allergic Conjunctivitis</b></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Can you describe the discharge? What color is it,
          and is it watery, sticky, or stringy?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Radiation (of Pain/Swelling) -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Radiation (of Symptoms)</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="infectious emergency">Swelling/redness of the eyelids is
              a red flag for periorbital cellulitis.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Is there any redness or swelling on the eyelids or
          around the eye itself?"</span></div>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>: Associated Symptoms</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Itching / Eye Rubbing:</b> <b class="rheumatic">Dominant
                feature of Allergic Conjunctivitis</b></li>
            <li><b>Redness (Conjunctival Injection):</b> Is it mild (pink) or
              fiery red?</li>
            <li><b>Eyelid Matting/Sticking:</b> Especially upon waking. <b class="infectious">Classic
                for Bacterial Conjunctivitis</b>.</li>
            <li class="infectious respiratory"><b>Upper Respiratory Symptoms
                (Cough, Coryza):</b> <span class="infectious">Strongly suggests
                Viral Conjunctivitis (adenovirus).</span></li>
            <li class="infectious ent"><b>Ear Pain / Ear Infection:</b> <span class="infectious">Conjunctivitis-Otitis
                Syndrome (often H. influenzae).</span></li>
            <li class="infectious"><b>Fever:</b> Suggests a systemic infection.</li>
            <li class="rheumatic"><b>History of Atopy (Eczema, Asthma, Allergic
                Rhinitis):</b> <span class="rheumatic">Increases suspicion for
                Allergic Conjunctivitis.</span></li>
            <li class="derma infectious emergency">Vesicles (blisters) on the
              skin around the eye or face? -&gt; <b class="emergency">Concern
                for Herpes (HSV/VZV)</b></li>
            <li class="obstetric infectious"><b>Maternal History:</b> STI
              exposure, HIV status, prophylaxis given?</li>
            <li class="infectious"><b>Recent Travel:</b> Exposure pathogens?</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Besides the eye issue, has your child had any
          other symptoms like a fever, cough, runny nose, or ear pain?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Progression</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Progression from one eye to the other is classic for viral
              conjunctivitis.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Has it gotten worse since it started? Did it begin
          in one eye and then spread to the other?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Is it worse at a particular time of day, like in
          the morning?"</span></div>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect on Life</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How is your child doing overall? Are they
          irritable, feeding and playing normally? Have they been sent home from
          daycare?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red Flags</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="ophthalmology emergency"><b>SIGNIFICANT PAIN or
                PHOTOPHOBIA (light sensitivity).</b></li>
            <li class="ophthalmology emergency"><b>CHANGE IN VISION</b> (as
              reported by parent or older child).</li>
            <li class="infectious ophthalmology emergency"><b>Swelling, redness,
                and tenderness of the Eyelids</b> (Periorbital/Orbital
              Cellulitis).</li>
            <li class="ophthalmology emergency">A cloudy cornea or abnormally
              shaped pupil.</li>
            <li class="obstetric infectious emergency"><b>ANY purulent discharge
                in the first month of life</b> (Ophthalmia Neonatorum).</li>
            <li class="derma infectious emergency">Blisters on the skin near the
              eye (Herpes).</li>
            <li class="ophthalmology emergency"><b>Severe eye pain or inability
                to open eye</b></li>
            <li class="emergency"><b>Systemic toxicity</b> (lethargy, poor
              feeding, high fever)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"I just need to ask some specific questions to make
          sure we're not missing anything serious."</span></div>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity / Bother Scale</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how much does this seem to
          be bothering your child?"</span></div>
    </div>
    <script src="harsha_iframe_youtube_player.js"></script>
